<title type="html"><![CDATA[Grond's Final Fantasy++ and WoC Reproduction?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3468&amp;p=25671#p25671"><![CDATA[
If you merge the two ROMs into a 512K chip, you'll need the SUROM board to play the result.  It should be fairly easy to add the 256K switching to the code, provided there's enough space (the original FF has quite a bit of space, but the space may have been used up in making the hack).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=360">dvdmth</a> — Mon Jul 02, 2007 10:09 am</p><hr />
